snippet.textDisplay:
Sure this so called " team " won against Braga ,, won by sheer luck and that's all. They ( Rangers ) desperately need every available point to even keep sight of Celtic. Here they are playing against a team that's three quarters of the way down the league and have won only seven games in twenty seven matches and the game ends in a tie ,, oh wow ,, one point !!
They ( Rangers ) are going to need a hell of a lot more than Gerrard and the latest and greatest Hagi for next season. They have no opportunity of winning the league title whatsoever now, the actual reality is that Glasgow Celtic operate as a team, a real team, Rangers do not.
Glasgow Rangers are simply a creature of their own demise, I've seen them play enough games without the slightest hint of commitment, the fans are the ones that have been let down. Best way to shake up this sad excuse for a team is to keep the stands empty, and good luck when Braga arrives at Ibrox, you're sure going to need it !!
